Lumnitzera racemosa

   [7429.jpg]
    Authority   Willd.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Myrtales:Combretaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 7429

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Troup R 1921 pp 496 548 [DRA, SAL, USE]
   Tomlinson P 1986 pp 225 [SAL]
   Aronson J 1989 pp 59 [SAL]
   White F 1983 pp 261 263 264
   National RC 180 pp 52-54 [DRA, SAL, TEXT, TEMP, KTMP, RAIN, DEP]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial evergreen shrub or small tree. In India kirpa flowers in
   March-April and fruit in September. (GMIN and GMAX estimated by the
   compiler).
   COMMON NAMES
   Kirpa, Yinye.
   FURTHER INF
   Adapted to the conditions in mangrove swamps, and under these
   conditions it can withstand mean annual rainfall as low as 100 mm.
   Otherwise a minimum yearly rainfall of 800 mm is required.
   Photosynthesis pathway C3.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
